 egin{align}(m - 1) + (m + 1) &= 52\end{align}  
The terms "$$m - 1$$" and "$$m + 1$$" represent two consecutive numbers with "$$m$$"  being their middle value. Simplifying the left-hand side:  
 egin{align}m - 1 + m + 1 &=52 \\2m &= 52\end{align}  

Dividing both sides by 2 to isolate "$$m$$":
   egin{align}m &= \frac{52}{2}\\m &= 26\end{align}
